[{"id":"VR058568","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR058554.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Examining the countries shown in white on the map of the former Yugoslavia, which of the following explains why the area would be referred to as a shatterbelt region?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR058568_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">EUROPEAN UNION 2018</p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a regional political map titled “European Union, 2018.” A key indicates that shaded countries are members of the European Union. The following countries are shaded as part of the European Union: Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, and the United Kingdom. The countries of Russia and Turkey are labeled on the map.\" height=\"365\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR058554.g06.png\" width=\"500\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">COUNTRIES OF THE FORMER YUGOSLAVIA</p>\n</div>\n<img alt=\"The figure presents a regional political map titled “Countries of the Former Yugoslavia.” The map shows the following countries: part of Italy, Slovenia, Croatia, part of Hungary, part of Romania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia, Montenegro, Kosovo, part of Albania, and North Macedonia. The Adriatic Sea is also indicated on the map. A key indicates that gray shaded countries represent European Union member states, and that the former Yugoslavia is outlined. All countries that are not shaded gray are shown in white. Countries shaded gray, which represent European Union member states, include: Italy, Slovenia, Croatia, Hungary, and Romania. The countries shown in white include: Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia, Montenegro, Kosovo, Albania, and North Macedonia. The following countries are located within the outline that indicates the former Yugoslavia: Slovenia, Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia, Montenegro, Kosovo, and North Macedonia.\" height=\"364\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR058554.g04.png\" width=\"500\" />\n<p class=\"attribution author\">Source: Natural Earth GIS</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The countries comprise a strategically positioned area and have unstable national governments.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The countries have an open-border policy and have abolished all passport and customs controls along their shared political boundaries.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The countries comprise a multiethnic culture region and have strong federal governments.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The countries are outside of the European Union but are inside of the European continent.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The countries are former communist states and remain allied with the Russia.</p>"],"answer":0}]